3 79-1054 (1)(a) This subsection applies until July 1, 2024.
4 (b) The State Board of Education shall establish a competitive
5 innovation grant program with funding from the Nebraska Education
6 Improvement Fund pursuant to section 79-3501. Grantees shall be a school
7 district, an educational service unit, or a combination of entities that
8 includes at least one school district or educational service unit. For
9 grantees that consist of a combination of entities, a participating
10 school district or educational service unit shall be designated to act as
11 the fiscal agent and administer the program funded by the grant. The
12 state board shall only award grants pursuant to applications that the
13 state board deems to be sufficiently innovative and to have a high chance
14 of success.
15 (c) An application for a grant pursuant to this subsection shall
16 describe:
17 (i) Specific measurable objectives for improving education outcomes
18 for early childhood students, elementary students, middle school
19 students, or high school students or for improving the transitions
20 between any successive stages of education or between education and the
21 workforce;
22 (ii) The method for annually evaluating progress toward a measurable
23 objective, with a summative evaluation of progress submitted to the state
24 board and electronically to the Education Committee of the Legislature on
25 or before July 1, 2019;
26 (iii) The potential for the project to be both scalable and
27 replicable; and
28 (iv) Any cost savings that could be achieved by reductions in other
29 programs if the funded program is successful.
30 (d) Based on evaluations received on or before July 1, 2019, for
31 each grant, the State Board of Education shall recommend the grant
